1. To help executives understand how information systems can enable change, it's a good idea to:
solution : D. Describe how the system can enable business innovation and help customers

2. A best practice for handling a large volume of system change requests is to:
solution : C. Assemble a governance team to help prioritize requests

3. Based on the TAM, before you implement system changes, you can increase the potential for user adoption by:
solution : A. Making sure users perceive the changes to be both useful and easu to use
